						<summary><p>#14: a) Agnīśvara temple, Tirukkāṭṭupaḷḷi, Tirukkāṭṭupaḷḷi taluk, Tañcāvūr district; b) on a pillar used as stepping stone in the southern entrance to the Nāṭarāja-<foreign>mandapa</foreign>; c) Regnal year 11 of Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ; d) are 1960–1961, no. 318 (+ p. 20); tli Tj 2892; iep 37; e) inscription not located personally; f) I visited the temple in November 2016, but I was not given access to the entrance of the Nāṭarāja-<foreign>maṇḍapa </foreign>to see the inscription. Fortunately, Arlo Griffiths photographed the estampage stored in the offices of the asi in Mysore, and I was therefore able to amend slightly the edition provided in iep 37.</p>

</summary>
